        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare distal hereditary motor neuropathy with a variable clinical phenotype typically characterized by congenital non-progressive predominantly distal lower limb muscle weakness and atrophy and congenital (or early-onset) flexion contractures of the hip knee and ankle joints. Reduced or absent lower limb deep tendon reflexes skeletal anomalies (bilateral talipes equinovarus scoliosis kyphoscoliosis lumbar hyperlordisis) late ambulation waddling gait joint hyperlaxity and/or bladder and bowel dysfuntion are usually also associated."
        },
